Question : Check if two strings are anagrams of each other.

Solution :
 import java.util.*;

public class MyClass {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String a = "baac";
        String b = "cabc";
        
        int[] freq=new int[26];
        
        for(char c : a.toCharArray()){
            int index=c-'a';
            freq[index]++;    
        }
        for(char ch : b.toCharArray()){
            int index=ch-'a';
            freq[index]--;
        }
        for (int val : freq) {
            if (val != 0) {
                System.out.println(false);
                return;
            }
        }
        System.out.println(true); 
    }
}

Things I learnt : 
We create the index by subtracting the ASCII value of 'a' from the character, i.e., index = c - 'a', so 'a' maps to 0, 'b' to 1, and so on.
